				<td align="left" width="100%">
				<p>[<a href="research.html">Research</a>] [<a href="publications.html">Publications</a>] 
				[<a href="professional.html">Professional&nbsp;Activities</a>] [<a href="undergrad.html">Undergrad</a>] 
				[<a href="people.html">People</a>] [<a href="personal.html">Personal</a>] 
				[<a href="links.html">Links</a>]</p>
				<p>Prof. Wong received the BEng degree in Computer Engineering, with
				first class honors, from the Chinese University of Hong Kong in 
				1998. From 1998 to 2001, he studied in United Kingdom at the University 
				of Cambridge, where he was a member of the Speech, Vision and Robotics 
				Group in the Department of Engineering. He received the MPhil and 
				PhD degrees, both in Computer Vision (Information Engineering), 
				from the University of Cambridge in 2000 and 2001, respectively.</p>
				<p>Since 2001, he has joined The University of Hong Kong, where he is now a Professor. He served as the Associate Head of the 
				Department of Computer Science from 2008 to 2012, and as the Programme Director of 
				the BEng(CompSc) programme from 2008 to 2015. He has been 
				appointed as the Deputy Director of <a href="http://ailt.cds.hku.hk/" target="_blank">AI Literacy Unit (AiLU)</a> since April 2025, and as the 
				Associate Head (Teaching &amp; Learning) of the 
				<a href="http://ai.hku.hk/" target="_blank">Division of AI &amp; Data Science</a> of the 
				<a href="http://www.cds.hku.hk/" target="_blank">School of 
				Computing &amp; Data Science</a> since June 2025.</p>
				<p>Prof. Wong's research interests are in <em> Computer Vision</em> and	<em>Machine Intelligence</em>. 
				He is the Director of the <a href="http://www.visionlab.cs.hku.hk/index.html" target="_blank">
				Computer Vision Laboratory</a>. His research works include camera calibration, shape and motion 
				recovery, face sketch synthesis and recognition, scene text recognition, 
				object retrieval, medical image understanding, and generative AI. He has published 
				over 180 peer-reviewed journal and conference papers. Many of his 
				works appear in top venues, including CVPR, ECCV, and ICCV (top 
				conferences in computer vision), and TPAMI, IJCV, and TIP (top journals 
				in computer vision). He is currently an	Associate Editor of 
				<a href="https://link.springer.com/journal/11263" target="_blank">IJCV</a>. 
				He regularly serves in the program committee of all major conferences 
				in computer vision and AI, including CVPR, ECCV, ICCV, NeurIPS, 
				ICML, ICLR, and 
				AAAI. He is also a regular reviewer of TPAMI, IJCV, and TIP.</p>
